A utility-based model predicting responder acceptance by combining sensitivity to proportional fairness (difference between actual and deserved share), own monetary gain, and a constant bias. The model uses three learnable parameters with generous, finite bounds: fairness sensitivity (alpha_fairness), self-interest (beta_self), and bias. Utility is mapped to choice probability via a logistic function.
</SUMMARY>

